## Normative promises

This repository represents OUGHT rules under `.norms/` using the `normative-promises` skill.

- Promise declarations never contain kept, broken, compliance, status, or trust fields.
- Promises inherit from their declaring domain into descendant domains while retaining their canonical address.
- Assessments are append-only, assessor-relative claims tied to evidence and a repository revision.
- Trust is a derived observer-relative score and must always include coverage and policy context.
- Use `.agents/skills/normative-promises/SKILL.md` for normative declaration, assessment, repair, or trust tasks.
